EX1:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h2>JavaScript Comments,Variables,statements</h2>

<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
var price1 = 5; //declaring and assigning
var price2 = 6;
var total = price1 + price2;
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML =
"The total is: " + total;
</script>

</body>
</html>
EX2:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h2>JavaScript Variables</h2>

<p>Strings are written with quotes.</p>
<p>Numbers are written without quotes.</p>

<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
var pi = 3.14;
var person = "John Doe";
var answer = 'Yes I am!';

document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML =
pi + "<br>" + person + "<br>" + answer;
</script>

</body>
</html>
